- Structured the notebook sections
- Loaded and validated CSV transaction data
- Calculated total spending
- Analysed spending by category
- Created charts and visualisations
- Built the budget tracking system

---

Reflection

At the beginning of the project, I found the assignment difficult because it involved many different components such as CSV analysis, chatbot integration, Gradio, testing, and documentation.

Breaking the project into smaller sections made the assignment much easier to manage. One of the most important lessons I learned during this stage was the importance of planning before coding. Organising the notebook and repository structure early reduced confusion during later development stages.

I also improved my understanding of how Python can process and analyse financial datasets using Pandas and Matplotlib.

During development, I encountered issues with CSV loading inside Google Colab because the notebook could not automatically access the CSV file stored in GitHub. After debugging the problem, I solved the issue by manually uploading the dataset into Colab before loading it into a Pandas DataFrame.

This experience helped me better understand file handling and debugging within notebook environments.

