Final Reflection

This project significantly improved my understanding of Python programming, debugging, financial data analysis, and project structure.

One of the most valuable lessons I learned was that planning and organisation are extremely important during software development. Breaking the assignment into smaller development stages made the project more manageable and reduced confusion throughout coding.

I also improved my understanding of debugging and validation. Throughout development, I encountered issues involving CSV loading, file handling, and function integration. Solving these problems helped me better understand how notebook environments and Python applications operate.

Another important learning experience was understanding how AI tools can support programming and learning responsibly. AI assistance helped explain concepts, improve readability, support debugging, and organise the development workflow. However, I still needed to understand, modify, test, and integrate the code myself to ensure the project worked correctly.

Overall, this project improved my confidence in Python programming and helped me better understand how programming can be used to solve practical business and finance problems.

